<refentry id="package.versioncontrol.hg.versioncontrol-hg.--get">
 <refnamediv>
  <refname>
   <function>VersionControl_Hg::__get</function>
  </refname>
  <refpurpose>Returns an object, usually handled by a command</refpurpose>
 </refnamediv>
 <refsynopsisdiv>
  <funcsynopsis>
   <funcsynopsisinfo>require_once &apos;/Hg.php&apos;;</funcsynopsisinfo>
   <funcprototype>
    <funcdef>
     mixed
     <function>VersionControl_Hg::__get</function>
    </funcdef>
    <paramdef>
     string
     <parameter>$name</parameter>
    </paramdef>
   </funcprototype>
  </funcsynopsis>
 </refsynopsisdiv>
 <refsect1 id="package.versioncontrol.hg.versioncontrol-hg.--get.desc">
  &title.desc;
  <para>A $name is a lowercase, short name of the object:  $hg-&gt;executable is an instance of VersionControl_Hg_Executable and can  be echoed to invoke __toString() to get a pertinent piece of metadata.</para>
  <para>
   Instead of calling:
   <programlisting role="php">
<![CDATA[$hg->getVersion();]]>
   </programlisting>
   ,  we simplify:
   <programlisting role="php">
<![CDATA[$version = $hg->version]]>
   </programlisting>
   .
  </para>
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 id="package.versioncontrol.hg.versioncontrol-hg.--get.param">
  &title.param;
  <para>
   <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
     <term>
      &type.string;
      <parameter>$name</parameter>
     </term>
     <listitem>
      <para>The object to get</para>
     </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
  </para>
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 id="package.versioncontrol.hg.versioncontrol-hg.--get.throws">
  &title.throws;
  <para>
   <emphasis>throws</emphasis>
   no exceptions thrown
  </para>
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 id="package.versioncontrol.hg.versioncontrol-hg.--get.note">
  &title.note;
  &note.notstatic;
</refsect1>
</refentry>
